content.description: Some sloping holds at the bottom and a little traverse right lead to jug-hauling and then a traverse left to the chains.
content.protection:
4 bolts

Shares anchor with the route to the left, Chain Gain.

Please note there’s only one one link on the left anchor bolt
content.location: On the main prow as you enter from the trail, to the right of Chain Gain

content.description:
A 2 pitch or one long pitch. There is an anchor at about 40 feet, traverse right and up through some interesting rock to upper anchors.

A fun climb, recommend long slings on some of the poorly placed bolts. The top anchor needs replacing.
content.location: left of Give until it hurts, directly in front of where the approach trail comes to the wall.

content.description: From the chains at the top of Chain Gang and Shelf Serve, traverse left and pull the roof, then continue up the overhanging face to chains just over the lip.
content.location: On top of Chain Gang and Shelf Serve, to the left.

content.description: Fun jug-hauling up a steep section of Relief Camp.  Start on a ramp and traverse right to gain the route.  Pull through a series of overhanging moves on good holds, clipping an extended bolt with a chain on it, before reaching the anchor.
content.location: Starts on the obvious right-trending ramp just up and right from where the trail comes in.  Stay straight to avoid the 10b which forks to the left about half-way up.

content.description: Pull over the strenuous roof around the mid point of this route.
Romp up overhanging jugs, trending slightly right until moving back left to the last bolt and further left to the anchor.  Fun movement, but short-lived.
content.protection: Lots of bolts packed into the short route.  6?
content.location: Immediately left of Jugular Vein.  Immediately right of Rhino Relief.

content.description: Overhanging climbing to start, a bit more vertical later.
Start as for Jugular, but then take the left fork at the split.
Climb up just right of the overhanging chains and then move up to the left of them once you are above.
On the prow, climb blocky features up a vertical section to an off-vertical finish at chains.  Pretty short, but a few fun moves.
content.protection:
3 bolts

Shares anchor with the route to the right, Shelf Service.

Please note there’s only one one link on the left anchor bolt
content.location: Prow just left of the access trail. To the right of Complete Overhaul and to the left of Shelf Service.

content.description: The start is wandering and funky. Use a runner on the first 2 bolts ( see below ) Very pumpy and overhanging start with great holds. Once you make it the crux ( about 3/4 of the way up ) its gets bit harder with small holds. Very fun climb!
content.location: From the Belay platform above "Shelf Serve" and "Chain Gain"  Traverse 6 feet right to find the first clip that is out of view. Use a full length runner for this clip!! ( and maybe even the second clip ) From here the climb heads left, above the hanging chain, and then upwards onto the face/arete ( right hand side of the headwall) Climber can be lowered all the way down to the ground, or bypass this all together by climbing Shelf Serve and Chain GANG as one continuous route. There will be severe road drag either way, but its worth it, Very fun exposed route!
